The paper deals with optimization problems in the context of automated reasoning and formal verification, which are typically studied in the subfield of logic and computation (cs.LO). The paper also discusses the use of SMT solvers, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data structures (cs.DS) research. Additionally, the paper presents an implementation within the MathSAT SMT solver, which falls under the subfield of programming languages (cs.PL) and software engineering (cs.SE).
